    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.6.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo; 8.2.3489\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 12.3\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\nUsing `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua` where `minimal.lua` contains:\r\n\r\n```\r\nvim.cmd 'highlight MsgArea guifg=#aeafb0 guibg=NONE gui=NONE guisp=NONE'\r\nprint(\"TEST TEST TEST\")\r\n```\r\nThe `highlight` command causes the message area to be cleared such that the `print` flashes by in a millisecond. When there are 2 `print` statement this is not a problem as the pager is invoked before nvim draws the initial screen.\r\n\r\nvim (not nvim) invokes the pager on a single print so this is not a problem on vim.\r\n\r\nNote: I first noticed this issue using the NightFox theme and have an open problem there (https://github.com/EdenEast/nightfox.nvim/issues/98). I narrowed it down to the single highligh command show above.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nExpected that a single print statement would be readable, either by be left in the MsgArea or by invoking the pager on startup. This is only a problem on startup.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nI've got nothing new to say here!",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
